    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 2,
      "id": "notes_t",
      "x": 100,
      "y": 800,
      "width": 1120,
      "height": 110,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 25,
      "text": "Key points\n• Parent agent uses each child agent's description to route NL questions (no data is duplicated).\n• Each Fabric data agent can attach up to 5 data sources (Lakehouse, Warehouse, KQL DB, Semantic Model, Mirrored DB).\n• Parent agents currently support up to ~5 child agents; all must live in F64+ capacity workspaces.\n• Identity flows through Entra ID; per-source RLS/OLS/CLS is honored at query time.\n• External consumers (Copilot Studio, Foundry agents, custom apps) call the parent OR individual child agents via the AI Foundry / OpenAI-compatible endpoint.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Key points\n• Parent agent uses each child agent's description to route NL questions (no data is duplicated).\n• Each Fabric data agent can attach up to 5 data sources (Lakehouse, Warehouse, KQL DB, Semantic Model, Mirrored DB).\n• Parent agents currently support up to ~5 child agents; all must live in F64+ capacity workspaces.\n• Identity flows through Entra ID; per-source RLS/OLS/CLS is honored at query time.\n• External consumers (Copilot Studio, Foundry agents, custom apps) call the parent OR individual child agents via the AI Foundry / OpenAI-compatible endpoint.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 14,
      "versionNonce": 498467806,
      "index": "aO",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776880172182,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "autoResize": true
    },
